Original Author: Unknown Remake Author: Silent Ricochet Custom Models: Shiroko Custom Bump-Maps: Silent Ricochet NOW WITH FULLY FUNCTIONING CUSTOM NAVIGATION MESH, FOR BOTS This map was inspired by a terribly made, but none-the-less, fun FY map. It takes on a jungle / ruins (or tropical) theme, with ruins on both sides, tropical foliage, a stagnant pond in the middle with a rope bridge across the small canyon. The original map for 1.6 was very Terrorist sided (they had tons of cover, while the CTs had almost none), So I added some of my own little touches. The original map wasn't ruins / jungle themed. It was a box and mis-aligned textures and walls out of no where (shitty map, but still fun). Also the map had tons of weapons lying around. After a quick poll among 15 members of FPS I decided to make it a Deagle map for more of a challenge and no gay sniping. I also bumpmapped a few Valve textures to make them look nice and give brushes more of a gritty 3d look to them. The textures are included in the pack. Have fun :) -Silent Ricochet

This map is a classic recreation of Nintendo's GoldenEye 64 map "The Stack," which is the top half of The Library. This map was made from scratch by me, Draven. The textures are from the GoldenEye: Source Team. This is a classic map with 3 very minor differences:
  1. The doors open On Touch AND On Use. In GoldenEye they only work on use, but due to people that can't figure out how to open a door, I put in the On Touch feature as well.
  2. The glass respawns after 45 seconds. it doesn't in GoldenEye.
  3. There was no jump in GoldenEye, so you couldn't "fall" off the edges. That has been removed so you can jump on to ramps and off of the top level.
This map is made for Gun Games and Fight Yards. There are 32 spawn points, but no bomb zones or hostages. **UPDATE** I have updated this map to 1.1 with changes including:
  1. Buy zones now fixed and cover all spawn points
  2. Fixed some texture misalignment
  3. Reduced file size by 500kb
I hope you enjoy this map. You can look forward to The Basement in the near future. The Library is located here: http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/58331 Please leave an assessment!

This map is a classic recreation of Nintendo's GoldenEye 64 map "The Library," which is The Stack with The Basement doors open. This map was made from scratch by me, Draven. The textures are from the GoldenEye: Source Team.

This is a classic map with 3 very minor differences:

1) The doors open On Touch AND On Use. In GoldenEye they only work on use, but due to people that can't figure out how to open a door, I put in the On Touch feature as well.

2) The glass respawns after 45 seconds. it doesn't in GoldenEye

3) There was no jump in GoldenEye, so you couldn't "fall" off the edges. Since you can jump in CS:S, that has not been included. You can jump on to ramps and off of the top level.

**NOTE**
In the basement, near the T spawn point, there is a very dark hall and you can't see the door. This is in GoldenEye, it is NOT a lighting mistake.

This map is made for Gun Games and Fight Yards, BUT is best played on Death Match. There are 32 spawn points, but no bomb zones or hostages. Buy zones cover the entire basement and first floor (just because i hate dealing with them and will change in the final version).
